<i>We started from the top,
where almost everything is ready.</i>

754
01:07:12,628 --> 01:07:14,505
<i>Yeah, but something
with the basement too?</i>

755
01:07:14,505 --> 01:07:16,465
<i>The cellar has long
been ready.</i>

756
01:07:21,678 --> 01:07:23,972
<i>Donut with chocolate icing.</i>

757
01:07:23,972 --> 01:07:26,683
<i>No, I don't like chocolate.</i>

758
01:07:26,683 --> 01:07:30,020
Hey Hachi,
what are you doing here?

759
01:07:30,020 --> 01:07:32,648
Look it... look it!

760
01:07:36,026 --> 01:07:38,487
He's staying right in the
same spot.

761
01:07:38,487 --> 01:07:41,490
<i>- I thought he moved away.
- He did.</i>

762
01:07:41,490 --> 01:07:47,077
- He looks hungry, huh.
- You're a softie, Jess.

763
01:07:47,078 --> 01:07:48,497
<i>We must give him a little.</i>

764
01:07:48,497 --> 01:07:54,263
<i>Hey, Hachi! Want a hotdog, bud?
Come on, boy.</i>

765
01:07:57,057 --> 01:07:57,497
Hachi!

766
01:07:58,215 --> 01:08:00,425
<i>Maybe he don't likes your
cooking, Jess.</i>

767
01:08:00,425 --> 01:08:03,970
This is Jess special. Come on, lick it.
You'll like it. It's good for you.

768
01:08:11,061 --> 01:08:12,937
Where did he comes from?

769
01:08:12,937 --> 01:08:16,066
Just show up.
Come on boy! Eat it.

770
01:08:16,066 --> 01:08:21,279
Oh... you better be careful. Hachi
got hotdogs in there older than you.

771
01:08:21,279 --> 01:08:23,615
Don't listen to them.

772
01:08:38,504 --> 01:08:39,672
Hachi.

773
01:08:39,672 --> 01:08:40,965
Oh, God.

774
01:08:41,007 --> 01:08:44,010
Hi! Oh... hi, I was so worried
about you...

775
01:08:46,804 --> 01:08:48,389
<i>I need you.</i>

776
01:08:48,389 --> 01:08:50,683
And why does she just
hanging around him for?

777
01:08:50,683 --> 01:08:54,645
<i>This the professor's daughter.
He probably lived with them.</i>

778
01:08:54,645 --> 01:08:56,731
<i>And Hachi ran out?</i>

779
01:08:56,731 --> 01:08:57,774
<i>Disappeared?</i>

780
01:08:57,774 --> 01:08:59,150
<i>Oh, dear God...</i>

781
01:08:59,150 --> 01:09:01,235
Will you come home with me?

782
01:09:02,153 --> 01:09:03,196
Hey, hey, hey, hey, she took it.

783
01:09:03,197 --> 01:09:04,238
It's alright. It's okay.

784
01:09:04,238 --> 01:09:05,615
It's okay.

785
01:09:06,324 --> 01:09:08,712
- Come on, come on
- Let's go, buddy.

786
01:09:09,243 --> 01:09:10,477
Thank you very much.

787
01:09:11,182 --> 01:09:11,882
Thank you!

788
01:09:17,585 --> 01:09:21,464
- That's the best stuff.
- Alright, get me a coffee.

789
01:09:23,132 --> 01:09:25,426
Jess, come on, pour me a coffee.

790
01:09:39,482 --> 01:09:43,235
I think of him too, everyday.

791
01:10:11,597 --> 01:10:12,765
Hey.

792
01:10:12,765 --> 01:10:19,438
You know we love you Hachi.
We want you to stay here with us.

793
01:10:22,774 --> 01:10:27,779
If you've to go, that's okay too.

794
01:10:29,865 --> 01:10:31,408
Okay!

795
01:10:49,885 --> 01:10:51,970
Bye, Hachi.

796
01:11:03,648 --> 01:11:05,942
Good afternoon, Hachi.

797
01:11:36,139 --> 01:11:42,228
Hey Hachi, here you go.
Don't tell Myra, alright!

798
01:11:44,230 --> 01:11:46,190
Good night, Hachi.

799
01:12:10,673 --> 01:12:14,135
<i>- Good morning, Jess.
- Hello, how are you?</i>

800
01:12:14,135 --> 01:12:17,889
<i>- I think a big hot dog and
two donuts. - Okay.</i>

801
01:12:24,353 --> 01:12:26,981
<i>Be careful, it's hot.</i>

802
01:12:31,861 --> 01:12:34,697
<i>Lucky, let's go!</i>

803
01:12:34,697 --> 01:12:37,074
Come on, sweetie.
Hey, Lucky!

804
01:12:37,074 --> 01:12:40,619
- Your coffee, enjoy your meal.
- Here girl. Come on Lucky, let's go.

805
01:12:47,710 --> 01:12:51,046
- Oh, excuse me, sir. - Uh-hmm?
- That dog out there...

806
01:12:51,463 --> 01:12:52,840
Yeah?

807
01:12:52,840 --> 01:12:55,968
Is that the dog that I've been
hearing so much about?

808
01:12:58,053 --> 01:12:59,930
What's it to you?

809
01:12:59,930 --> 01:13:04,727
Oh, I am sorry. I'm Teddy Barnes,
I'm with the Metro <i>The Call.</i>

810
01:13:05,936 --> 01:13:09,189
Yeah, I've been hearing a lot
of talks about him on the train.

811
01:13:09,189 --> 01:13:12,443
I don't know. Sounds like
it could make a good story.

812
01:13:15,154 --> 01:13:17,656
That's Boilils, Carl Boilils.

813
01:13:17,656 --> 01:13:21,076
B-o-i-l-i-l-s.

814
01:13:21,076 --> 01:13:22,119
- Yes, there's no 'Y' in there.
- Got it.

815
01:13:22,161 --> 01:13:25,247
I'm the one that found him,
handed him over.

816
01:13:25,289 --> 01:13:26,832
Oh yeah?

817
01:13:26,832 --> 01:13:31,211
So Carl... where does he live?

818
01:13:31,211 --> 01:13:36,008
Well... we're not really sure.
He comes and goes.

819
01:13:36,008 --> 01:13:38,719
- Nobody bothers him?
- No, we put up with him.

820
01:13:39,678 --> 01:13:41,430
He just does what's he is doing.

821
01:13:41,430 --> 01:13:46,435
Mind if I take a picture?
For the newspaper.

822
01:13:46,435 --> 01:13:49,146
Oh, I don't mind,
Hachi don't mind?

823
01:13:49,146 --> 01:13:51,022
Thank you very much.
Very nice... very nice.

824
01:13:51,022 --> 01:13:53,859
Er... one without first please.

825
01:13:53,859 --> 01:13:56,862
Not the dog, alright.
Stay there.

826
01:13:57,529 --> 01:13:59,489
Hmm... No, I...

827
01:14:00,157 --> 01:14:02,909
- Oh yeah, alright.
- I appreciated it.

828
01:14:02,909 --> 01:14:05,745
That's very kind of you.

829
01:14:06,830 --> 01:14:08,456
Okay, nice and easy.

830
01:14:08,456 --> 01:14:09,916
- Oh yeah!
- Yeah... yeah.

831
01:14:09,916 --> 01:14:12,002
Look there, big smile.

832
01:14:12,002 --> 01:14:14,379
Smile... Aah, that's...

833
01:14:15,579 --> 01:14:17,779
That's beautiful, thank you.

834
01:14:18,466 --> 01:14:22,220
<i>Faithful dog awaits return
of deceased master</i>

835
01:14:31,020 --> 01:14:32,522
Hey Hachi.

836
01:14:34,649 --> 01:14:38,486
This kid in Gary,
send you his lunch money.

837
01:14:38,486 --> 01:14:41,322
He ask me to buy you
treats with it.

838
01:14:42,615 --> 01:14:44,951
It's the third one this week.

839
01:14:44,951 --> 01:14:48,079
If this keeps up, I've gotta
open a bank account for you.

840
01:14:48,705 --> 01:14:50,790
Don't say I never gave you though.

841
01:14:54,127 --> 01:14:56,421
Dog's making it like a bandit here.

842
01:14:57,171 --> 01:14:59,674
Look at this! Isn't that cute?

843
01:15:00,758 --> 01:15:02,385
<i>Hey Hac!</i>

844
01:15:02,719 --> 01:15:05,096
- What're you doing with his money?
- I am his executor.

845
01:15:15,106 --> 01:15:17,400
- Be right with you, sir.
- Thank you.

846
01:15:33,040 --> 01:15:37,503
Hello Hachi, how are you?

847
01:15:39,213 --> 01:15:42,925
Here you are Hachi.
There you are.

848
01:15:43,718 --> 01:15:45,428
Hungry... eh?

849
01:15:45,428 --> 01:15:49,306
Yes, very cold. He must eat.

850
01:15:50,766 --> 01:15:53,769
I'm just Jess,
I run the hotdog stand.

851
01:15:53,769 --> 01:15:56,522
I'm Ken-Vijish,
Professor Wilson's friend.

852
01:15:56,522 --> 01:15:58,607
Mr. Professor, ha.

853
01:15:58,607 --> 01:16:01,235
One sugar, two creams.

854
01:16:02,361 --> 01:16:04,572
So then you must have
read the article then?

855
01:16:04,572 --> 01:16:05,614
I did!

856
01:16:05,614 --> 01:16:07,700
You saw my name in the article?

857
01:16:07,700 --> 01:16:09,868
Yes, I did. That...

858
01:16:09,868 --> 01:16:10,911
Twice.

859
01:16:11,245 --> 01:16:13,414
Please, let me help with the expense.

860
01:16:13,414 --> 01:16:15,708
No, no, no, please. No money.

861
01:16:15,708 --> 01:16:17,793
What if he get sick?
Medical expenses...

862
01:16:17,793 --> 01:16:20,567
They get collection,
from the travellers,

863
01:16:20,568 --> 01:16:23,340
the vendors and
we will take care of it.

864
01:16:23,340 --> 01:16:25,676
This station is where Hachi
roams now.

865
01:16:25,677 --> 01:16:28,011
Everyday he comes same time,
same place...

866
01:16:28,011 --> 01:16:29,471
... here only.

867
01:16:29,471 --> 01:16:31,056
You'll do that for him?

868
01:16:31,056 --> 01:16:32,808
Take care of him?

869
01:16:32,808 --> 01:16:34,393
Of course!

870
01:16:36,270 --> 01:16:40,524
Okay then.
Got to serve some hotdogs.

871
01:16:40,524 --> 01:16:41,567
Good to meet you.

872
01:16:41,567 --> 01:16:44,069
Me too.
Thank you very much.

873
01:17:30,782 --> 01:17:36,955
Come on, mister.
Here we go.

874
01:17:40,708 --> 01:17:44,879
Want some more?
Here, take this.

875
01:17:46,756 --> 01:17:51,636
Okay... come on boy, last piece.
Taste good, eh?

876
01:18:02,188 --> 01:18:03,731
<i>This is where you
all brought it?</i>

877
01:18:03,731 --> 01:18:06,859
<i>- Oh, thank you.
- See you tomorrow, Hachi.</i>

878
01:18:08,111 --> 01:18:09,904
<i>Ciao, Hachi!</i>

879
01:18:48,150 --> 01:18:49,735
<i>Thanks.</i>

880
01:19:02,832 --> 01:19:05,167
<i>The usual, eh?</i>

881
01:19:05,167 --> 01:19:07,753
<i>Why you ever not take
chicken wings?</i>

882
01:19:07,753 --> 01:19:08,796
<i>Hey, this...</i>

883
01:19:08,796 --> 01:19:09,838
<i>Mustard?</i>

884
01:19:10,881 --> 01:19:13,175
Mrs. Wilson, nice to 
see you again.

885
01:19:13,175 --> 01:19:14,218
Good afternoon.

886
01:19:16,095 --> 01:19:18,847
Hey, that's the professor's wife, eh?

887
01:19:29,650 --> 01:19:31,985
<i>Now Showing
The Merchant of Venice</i>

888
01:20:11,358 --> 01:20:15,570
<i>Parker H. Wilson
Loving husband and father</i>

889
01:20:18,907 --> 01:20:20,992
Cate.

890
01:20:24,621 --> 01:20:25,956
Ken...

891
01:20:28,667 --> 01:20:30,752
It's been awhile.

892
01:20:31,378 --> 01:20:33,463
Certainly have.

893
01:20:43,056 --> 01:20:47,852
It's been 10 years... 
can you believe it.

894
01:21:02,450 --> 01:21:04,243
Hi Hachi!

895
01:21:10,375 --> 01:21:12,877
<i>Good day, Hachi.</i>

896
01:21:26,432 --> 01:21:28,831
<i>Coffee without sugar, and don't
put mustard in the hot dog.</i>

897
01:21:28,832 --> 01:21:31,229
<i>Ketchup is the best.</i>

898
01:21:31,229 --> 01:21:33,314
<i>Alright, have a good one.</i>

899
01:21:57,004 --> 01:21:58,756
Hachi?

900
01:22:05,346 --> 01:22:07,431
Hachi...

901
01:22:11,268 --> 01:22:14,396
Oh, you poor thing,
you're still waiting.

902
01:22:25,366 --> 01:22:27,659
Good boy.

903
01:22:29,411 --> 01:22:32,539
Hachi!

904
01:22:47,471 --> 01:22:51,225
If it's alright, could I wait with
you for the next train?

905
01:22:54,019 --> 01:22:55,604
Yeah?

906
01:22:57,147 --> 01:22:59,232
Thanks.

907
01:23:07,991 --> 01:23:09,659
Oh, Hachi...

908
01:23:22,464 --> 01:23:23,507
<i>You're so tiny.</i>

909
01:23:23,548 --> 01:23:24,591
<i>You like that mom?</i>

910
01:23:24,591 --> 01:23:25,634
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

911
01:23:25,634 --> 01:23:27,594
Let's go somewhere.

912
01:23:27,594 --> 01:23:28,637
Oh, that's me.

913
01:23:28,637 --> 01:23:31,661
I know, I remember.

914
01:23:31,662 --> 01:23:34,684
I remember I was there that day
when the picture was taken.

915
01:23:35,644 --> 01:23:37,520
- He is so excited.
- Hmm!

916
01:23:39,189 --> 01:23:41,149
Oh, he's at the wedding.

917
01:23:41,149 --> 01:23:46,154
Yeah, he's right there.
Right there.

918
01:23:46,154 --> 01:23:48,573
Where did grandpa find Hachi?

919
01:23:49,699 --> 01:23:53,661
<i>Ronnie, actually Hachi found
your grandfather.</i>

920
01:23:53,661 --> 01:23:55,538
<i>How?</i>

921
01:23:55,538 --> 01:24:00,251
<i>One night, your grandfather
was coming back from a trip.</i>

922
01:24:01,794 --> 01:24:06,799
<i>Got out of the train station
and on the platform...</i>

923
01:26:00,579 --> 01:26:02,247
Hey, wake up.

924
01:26:02,247 --> 01:26:04,750
Hey, boy.

925
01:26:05,876 --> 01:26:09,629
Hey, come on. Let's go!

926
01:26:37,991 --> 01:26:39,659
Hachi!

927
01:26:39,659 --> 01:26:41,953
Hey boy!

928
01:27:24,287 --> 01:27:29,292
<i>I never met my grandfather.
He died when I was just a baby.</i>

929
01:27:29,333 --> 01:27:35,590
But when I hear about him and Hachi,
I feel like I know him.

930
01:27:35,590 --> 01:27:39,240
<i>They taught me the
meaning of loyalty, </i>

931
01:27:39,241 --> 01:27:42,889
<i>and you should never forget
anyone that you love.</i>

932
01:27:43,306 --> 01:27:47,685
And that's why Hachi  will
forever be my hero.

933
01:28:01,615 --> 01:28:03,743
Oh, he's happy to see somebody.

934
01:28:06,120 --> 01:28:07,788
Move along.

935
01:28:11,125 --> 01:28:13,627
Come on Hachi, let's go!

